  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because what happened was that [NON-ENGLISH] was given the task of doing an offensive, a counter-offensive, in the Belgian Ardennes in the winter of 1944 to try to change the tide of war, and also to give the, the Germans more time to develop their secret weapons, which were these, these, these, these-- the, the, the, the forerunners of the Scuds, you know, the flying missiles, the V-1s and V-2s, which were targeted at Antwerp and at London, England.",
      "word_count": 79
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "To give them more time, and they thought they were going to come up with some other secret weapons, such as-- they were working heavy water.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They were working, as we found out later, even on nuclear weapons.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So to buy time.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And all of a sudden because of the winter and bad visibility, and the American Air Force didn't have a-- couldn't, couldn't penetrate.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the two were locked behind us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then the episode with Skorzeny, as we know, with-- donning America uniforms and infiltrating.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So they were quite successful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They were coming back and in our direction.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we were nearby.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was a new panic there that, hey, the Germans are coming back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's not over.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They're going to finish off what they-- what they couldn't finish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We thought that they were going to come back and occupy us again.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's only when-- it's only the-- when Patton threw the counter, counter offensive and they changed the Battle of the Bulge.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was one anxiety.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The next thing was, that after the city was liberated, Antwerp, which is not often talked about, was also targeted as one of the, for the flying bombs, the V-1s, like London.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because they knew that Antwerp was going to be a big supply harbor for the Allied war effort.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
